re as different as land and sea. You feel physical pain if your arm breaks, and you feel mental pain if your heart breaks. Between these two different events we seem to imagine a gulf so wide and deep that it might as well be filled by a sea that is impossible to navigate.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPainxPsychological aspects. 0aPainxSocial aspects. 4aLiterary Criticism. 4aSemiotics & Theory. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh1 aMorris, David B., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052008276240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091382040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520913820423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520913820/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles